The paper deals with game theory and optimization in a market setting, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the use of strategic bidding and the study of Nash dynamics suggest that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of convergence results, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of algorithms and optimization techniques could also suggest the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the study of market equilibria and buyer-seller interactions could place it in the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-category.
